<content type="application/x.deki0805+xml" title="deck"><body xmlns:eval="http://mindtouch.com/2007/dekiscript"><div class="noinclude"><span class="script">template.XULRefElem()</span></div> <p>An element that displays only one of its children at a time. The <span class="script">template.XULAttr("selectedIndex")</span> attribute determines which child is displayed.
</p><p>More information is available in the <a href="en/XUL_Tutorial/Stacks_and_Decks">XUL tutorial</a>.
</p>
<dl><dt> Attributes
</dt><dd> <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("a-", "selectedIndex")</span>
</dd></dl>
<dl><dt> Properties
</dt><dd> <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("p-", "selectedIndex")</span>, <span class="script">template.PrefAnch("p-", "deck.selectedPanel", "selectedPanel")</span>
</dd></dl>
<h3 name="Examples"> Examples </h3>
<pre>
&lt;deck selectedIndex="2"&gt;
  &lt;description value="This is the first page"/&gt;
  &lt;button label="This is the second page"/&gt;
  &lt;box&gt;
    &lt;description value="This is the third page"/&gt;
    &lt;button label="This is also the third page"/&gt;
  &lt;/box&gt;
&lt;/deck&gt;
</pre>
